President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of South Dakota due to a severe winter storm, snowstorm, and flooding that occurred from October 3-16, 2013. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. Affected individuals in certain counties and tribes are eligible for Disaster Unemployment Assistance. Federal funding is also available for emergency work, facility repair or replacement, snow assistance, and hazard mitigation measures. Gary R. Stanley has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations. Additional designations may be made if requested by the state and further damage assessments warrant it.